# AGENTS.override.md - csharp_desktop

## Profile

csharp_desktop

## Purpose

Override base AGENTS.md guidance for a C# desktop or local tool project with solution/project structure and explicit script entrypoints.

## Read Order

1. AGENTS.md
2. AGENTS.override.md
3. PRODUCT.md
4. MVP.md
5. PROJECT_BOUNDARY.md
6. DATA_SCOPE.md
7. APPROVALS.md
8. PHASE_PLAN.md
9. STATUS.md
10. ACCEPTANCE_TRACE.md
11. SOURCE_INDEX.md
12. SAFETY_POLICY.profile.md
13. VERIFICATION.profile.md

## Expected Layout

- Solution file or project file at the repo root or under src/.
- build.ps1 documented as the build entrypoint when implemented.
- test.ps1 documented as the test entrypoint when implemented.
- smoke.ps1 documented as the smoke entrypoint when implemented.

## Phase Gate

Before implementation, confirm:
- Product and MVP contracts are current.
- Target project path is known.
- Build/test/smoke commands are documented or marked NOT RUN.
- GUI or desktop side effects are understood.

## P1 Template Boundary

This template does not create a solution, project, PowerShell scripts, or C# source code.

## Verification Defaults

- Build check through project-defined build.ps1 or equivalent.
- Test check through project-defined test.ps1 or equivalent.
- Smoke check through project-defined smoke.ps1 or manual smoke notes.
